.TH UP 1 "2026-02" "paw-proxy" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
up \- Dev server wrapper — register routes with paw\-proxy and run commands
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B up
.RB [ -n
.IR name ]
.RB [ \-\-restart ]
.I command
.RI [ args... ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B up
Dev server wrapper — register routes with paw\-proxy and run commands.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-n \fIname\fR
Custom domain name (default: package.json name or directory)
.TP
.B \-\-restart
Auto\-restart on crash (non\-zero exit)
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B PORT
Allocated port for your dev server to bind to
.TP
.B APP_DOMAIN
Domain name, e.g. myapp.test
.TP
.B APP_URL
Full URL, e.g. https://myapp.test
.TP
.B HTTPS
Always "true"
.TP
.B NODE_EXTRA_CA_CERTS
Path to CA cert (for Node.js HTTPS requests)
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Run Bun dev server with HTTPS:
.PP
.RS
.nf
$ up bun dev
.fi
.RE
.PP
Run npm dev server with HTTPS:
.PP
.RS
.nf
$ up npm run dev
.fi
.RE
.PP
Custom domain: https://api.test:
.PP
.RS
.nf
$ up \-n api bun dev
.fi
.RE
.PP
Auto\-restart on crash:
.PP
.RS
.nf
$ up \-\-restart bun dev
.fi
.RE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR paw-proxy(1)
